## The Alduin Incident

In 4E 201, **Alduin** was feeding on the souls of Sovngarde — devouring the dead to increase his power before destroying the world:
- He created an **impenetrable mist** around Sovngarde to disorient souls
- The ancient heroes could not fight him alone
- The Last Dragonborn entered Sovngarde through the portal at Skuldafn
- Together with Felldir, Gormlaith, and Hakon, he defeated Alduin for good
- Tsun returned the Dovahkiin to Mundus after the victory

## Shor

**Shor** is the Nordic aspect of Lorkhan — the dead god who created Mundus. He is the "king" of Sovngarde, but:
- His throne is **always empty** when visited
- He is "absent" — perhaps because Lorkhan is dead/dispersed
- Some theorize that he is still present but invisible to mortal eyes
- Others believe he periodically reincarnates as a Shezarrine

## Cultural Comparisons

Each culture has its own afterlife in Aetherius:
- **Nords** — Sovngarde (hall of Shor)
- **Redguards** — Far Shores
- **Khajiit** — The Sands Behind the Stars
- **Imperials** — Generic Aetherius (no specific named location)
- **Dunmer** — Join their ancestors (not Aetherius — ancestral tradition)

Are these separate planes or different regions of Aetherius? Tamriel's theologians are still debating.
